        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): wire message:sending internal hook to user-defined hooks",
        "body": "## Problem\nInternal `message_sending` hook fires only through the typed plugin hook runner and bridges only `message:sent` to internal hooks. User-defined hook handlers configured under `message:sending` never receive outbound message events.\n\nFixes #73542\n\n## Fix\nAdd an internal `message:sending` bridge with underscore-key dispatch (`message_sending` ↔ `message:sending`), wire it into core outbound delivery in `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts`, and update hook/outbound tests. Also adds heartbeat `message_tool_only` raw reply suppression to prevent tool-only responses from leaking through the hook bridge.\n\n## Test plan\n1. Verify `message:sending` fires through internal hook bridge\n2. Verify underscore-key dispatch works for both `message_sending` and `message:sending`\n3. Verify heartbeat tool-only replies are suppressed\n4. Run hook and outbound test suites\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts (tests pass)\n✓ src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts (tests pass)\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  112 passed (112)\n   Duration  9.54s\n```\n\nAll 112 hook and outbound delivery tests pass, covering the internal `message:sending` bridge, underscore-key dispatch, and heartbeat tool-only suppression.",
